Time taken 0.8/2.3 in both solution
In this question firstly get the max element of 1d array by just sorting it and the n-1 the element will be the maximum element.
In the 2d array want you have to do is you want the sum of left diagonal array i have thought of two ways like have two for loop of i,j and then if i==j then take the sum of left diagonal shown in below
ArrayList<Integer> res=new ArrayList<>();
        int leftdiagonal=0;
        Arrays.sort(b);
        int x=b[n-1];
        
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++)
        {
            for (int j=0;j<n;j++)
            {
                if(i==j)
                leftdiagonal=leftdiagonal+a[i][j];
            }
            
        }
        
        res.add(leftdiagonal);
         res.add(x);
        return res;
        or
        But I will personally say go for 2nd solution because it is slightly optimized.
        ArrayList<Integer> res=new ArrayList<>();
        int leftdiagonal=0;
        Arrays.sort(b);
        int x=b[n-1];
        
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++)
        {
            leftdiagonal=leftdiagonal+a[i][i];
            
        }
        
        res.add(leftdiagonal);
         res.add(x);
        return res;
